==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Sanskrit [[संस्कृतम्]] (saṃskṛtam) ‘perfected, prepared’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈsænskrɪt/}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# Any of the [[Old Indic]] languages, especially [[Classical Sanskrit]], a language of ancient [[India]] still important to [[Hinduism]] and [[Buddhism]].

